{
    "level": "A2",
    "intro": "In this topic, you will learn the <strong>formula of the passive voice</strong>: how V3 (Past Participle) is formed, the difference between regular and irregular verbs, and word order in passive sentences.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Formula",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "Base structure: <strong>be + Past Participle (V3)</strong>:",
            "example": "The letter is written."
        },
        {
            "label": "Regular V3",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "Regular verbs: <strong>V + -ed</strong>:",
            "example": "clean → cleaned, open → opened"
        },
        {
            "label": "Irregular V3",
            "color": "rose",
            "text": "Irregular verbs: <strong>special form</strong>:",
            "example": "write → written, make → made"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. The formula of the passive state",
    "intro": "The passive state is formed by the formula:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "be",
            "title": "The verb be",
            "subtitle": "Changes in time: am/is/are, was/were, will be, has been..."
        },
        {
            "label": "+",
            "title": "Plus",
            "subtitle": ""
        },
        {
            "label": "V3",
            "title": "Past Participle",
            "subtitle": "The third form of the verb: written, made, cleaned, built..."
        },
        {
            "label": "(by)",
            "title": "Agent (optional)",
            "subtitle": "Performer of the action: by Tom, by the company..."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Regular verbs (V3 = V2 = V + ed)",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Basic rule",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "For regular verbs <strong>Past Participle (V3) = Past Simple (V2)</strong>: add <strong>-ed</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "clean → cleaned → cleaned",
                    "ua": "clean → cleaned → cleaned"
                },
                {
                    "en": "open → opened → opened",
                    "ua": "open → opened → opened"
                },
                {
                    "en": "paint → painted → painted",
                    "ua": "paint → painted → painted"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Rules for writing -ed",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "Features of adding <strong>-ed</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Після -e: live → lived",
                    "ua": "Після -e: live → lived"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Після приголосної + y: study → studied",
                    "ua": "Після приголосної + y: study → studied"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Короткі з CVC: stop → stopped",
                    "ua": "Короткі з CVC: stop → stopped"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Irregular verbs — Table V3",
    "intro": "The most frequent irregular verbs for the passive:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "write",
            "ua": "write",
            "note": "written — The letter is written."
        },
        {
            "en": "make",
            "ua": "make",
            "note": "made — Cars are made in Germany."
        },
        {
            "en": "build",
            "ua": "build",
            "note": "built — The house was built in 1990."
        },
        {
            "en": "break",
            "ua": "break",
            "note": "broken — The window was broken."
        },
        {
            "en": "take",
            "ua": "take",
            "note": "taken — The photo was taken yesterday."
        },
        {
            "en": "give",
            "ua": "give",
            "note": "given — The prize was given to him."
        },
        {
            "en": "see",
            "ua": "see",
            "note": "seen — The film was seen by millions."
        },
        {
            "en": "do",
            "ua": "do",
            "note": "done — The work is done."
        },
        {
            "en": "send",
            "ua": "send",
            "note": "sent — The email was sent."
        },
        {
            "en": "buy",
            "ua": "buy",
            "note": "bought — The car was bought last week."
        },
        {
            "en": "sell",
            "ua": "sell",
            "note": "sold — All tickets were sold."
        },
        {
            "en": "steal",
            "ua": "steal",
            "note": "stolen — My bike was stolen."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Format: <strong>V1 — V2 — V3</strong> (Infinitive — Past — Past Participle)"
}

{
    "title": "4. Word order in the passive voice",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Affirmative",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Порядок: <strong>Subject + be + V3 (+ by agent)</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The letter is written.",
                    "ua": "The letter is written."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The letter is written by Tom.",
                    "ua": "The letter is written by Tom."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Cars are made in Japan.",
                    "ua": "Cars are made in Japan."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Denial",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "Order: <strong>Subject + be + not + V3</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The door is not locked.",
                    "ua": "The door is not locked."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The work was not finished.",
                    "ua": "The work was not finished."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Question",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "Order: <strong>Be + Subject + V3?</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Is the letter written?",
                    "ua": "Is the letter written?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Was the work finished?",
                    "ua": "Was the work finished?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Are cars made here?",
                    "ua": "Are cars made here?"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. Typical mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Omission of the verb be.",
            "wrong": "The letter written by Tom.",
            "right": "✅ The letter is written by Tom."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Using V2 instead of V3.",
            "wrong": "The house was builded.",
            "right": "✅ The house was built. (build-built-built)"
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Confusion of V2 and V3 for irregulars.",
            "wrong": "The window was broke.",
            "right": "✅ The window was broken. (break-broke-broken)"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "Other pages from the basics of the passive voice",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "What is Passive Voice?",
            "current": false
        },
        {
            "label": "Form: be + V3 (current)",
            "current": true
        },
        {
            "label": "Present Simple Passive",
            "current": false
        },
        {
            "label": "Past Simple Passive",
            "current": false
        }
    ]
}
